    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="427"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Dupuy de Lôme</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your excellency’s polite note, under date of 27th instant, in which
                    you are pleased to inform me of the falsity of the rumors of the departure of a
                    filibustering expedition from St. Tammany Parish, La.</p>
                <p>In giving your excellency my most sincere thanks for the investigations made,</p>
                <p>I improve, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Dupuy de Lôme.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
